  "hasContextOfUse": "{\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb\", \"type\": \"ContextOfUse\", \"name\": \"COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)\", \"description\": \"A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.\", \"deviceClass\": \"Class II\", \"decisionConsequence\": \"High\", \"modelInfluence\": \"Medium\", \"intendedUse\": \"Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).\", \"hasApplicabilityConstraint\": {\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/applicability-constraint\", \"type\": \"ApplicabilityConstraint\", \"name\": \"In-scope domain: FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB operating conditions\", \"description\": \"The model is applicable to Newtonian blood-analogue fluids at hematocrit 35–45%, pump rotational speeds of 2000–4000 RPM, and flow rates of 2–6 L/min representative of adult CPB procedures. The model is not applicable to pediatric pump geometries, pulsatile flow regimes, or operating points outside the specified speed-flow envelope. Hemolysis predictions are valid only for the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as defined in the Morrison 2022 benchmark dataset.\"}, \"hasOperatingEnvelope\": {\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/operating-envelope\", \"type\": \"OperatingEnvelope\", \"name\": \"CPB operating envelope: flow rate 2–6 L/min, speed 2000–4000 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%\", \"description\": \"Concrete operating bounds: volumetric flow rate Q ∈ [2.0, 6.0] L/min; impeller rotational speed N ∈ [2000, 4000] RPM; fluid hematocrit Hct ∈ [35, 45]%; inlet pressure p_in ∈ [5, 15] mmHg; outlet pressure head ΔP ∈ [50, 300] mmHg; blood temperature T ∈ [35, 38] °C; exposure time per pass τ ∈ [0.01, 0.5] s. All five benchmark operating points (2 L/min/2500 RPM, 3 L/min/3000 RPM, 4 L/min/3000 RPM, 5 L/min/3500 RPM, 6 L/min/4000 RPM) fall within these bounds. Extrapolation outside these ranges is not supported by the validation evidence.\"}}}",
